import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react'; const Analytics = ({ courses }) => { const [selectedCourseId, setSelectedCourseId] = useState(''); const [feedbackData, setFeedbackData] = useState(null); // Mock data - will be replaced with API call const mockFeedbackData = { averageRating: 4.2, totalFeedbacks: 25, ratingDistribution: [2, 3, 5, 10, 5] // [1-star, 2-star, 3-star, 4-star, 5-star] }; useEffect(() => { if (selectedCourseId) { // In a real app, we would fetch data for the selected course setFeedbackData(mockFeedbackData); } }, [selectedCourseId]); return (

Course Analytics

{feedbackData && ( <>
Average Rating

{feedbackData.averageRating}/5

Total Feedbacks

{feedbackData.totalFeedbacks}

Rating Distribution
1 Star:
{feedbackData.ratingDistribution[0]}
2 Stars:
{feedbackData.ratingDistribution[1]}
3 Stars:
{feedbackData.ratingDistribution[2]}
4 Stars:
{feedbackData.ratingDistribution[3]}
5 Stars:
{feedbackData.ratingDistribution[4]}
)}
); }; export default Analytics;
